In addition to the above Clean Air Act requirements, Clearwater is in compliance with the OSHA PSM, EPA SPCC, OSHA HAZWOPER, EPCRA, and EPA RCRA Contingency Planning requirements.  Clearwater has also conducted a process hazard analysis on processes that use formaldehyde processes, herein referred to as formalin or formaldehyde storage and processing or simply as the formaldehyde process.Clearwater has implemented safety precautions and procedures designed to prevent and mitigate catastrophic releases. Clearwter has active operatin, maintenance, training, and inspection preocedures; a trained Emergency Response Team and an evacuation plan for each area. In addition, Clearwater has communicated and coordinating response for site-specific chemical hazard information with the LEPC and local Emergency HAZMAT response team. .

Clearwater?s management is committed to the following:

? Preventing accidents;
? Training our employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;
? Participating in community emergency preparedness;
? Addressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with Clearwater operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents; and
? Being a good corporate citizen of Bexar County.

With these objectives in mind, this Risk Management Plan has been developed to provide information about Clearwater?s management of the risks associated with operating the batch specialty chemicals manufacturing plant.  Most important, we stress our commitment to ensuring a safe operation for our employees, our visitors, and our community.
